\f0\fs24 \cf0 "iPhone Buttons" is a webpage that displays a set of iPhone styled buttons using HTML and CSS technologies.\
This sample describes how to build five dynamic buttons that horizontally scale. They are 150 pixels wide. All text on the buttons is 20 pixels, Helvetica, black and bold. Each button was created using the -webkit-border-image property and a single PNG image in lieu of several images. Each PNG image is either 29x46 pixels or 18x30 pixels.\
\
The -webkit-border-image property divides an image into nine parts with two divisions on the vertical axis and two divisions on the horizontal axis (see Figure1). The -webkit-border-image property receives four values: first, second, third and fourth.\
The first and third values set the height of the image's top and bottom parts. The second and fourth attributes define the width of the right and left sides of the image.\
